$250 For sale is a 1942 Mosin 91/30 with ATI Monte Carlo Stock
All matching numbers on the barrel shank, magazine floor plate, and bolt.
Straight shooting Mosin.This rifle is a perfect platform to make a project. title: For Sale:  Winchester 63
postcontent: Used Winchester Model 63, in .22 LR, made in 1939. This rifle is in superb mechanical shape. In fact, I just test fired it again in my back yard, and rang the steel at 50 yards with no problem whatsoever. Way too much fun. The takedown feature also seems useful if you are the backpacking type. If you don't know much about this model, there are plenty of websites that sing its praises. All I can add to them is that it feels very well made. I love my marlin 60s and Ruger 10/22s, but this rifle feels like it is in an entirely different class. It is like when I traded in my old Infiniti for a Corolla. The Corolla is practical and works well, but it just doesn't drive the same. Anyway, this rifle, as evidenced by the pictures, has some cosmetic wear. It was stored in a basement for years, and there are some rust spots that have been cleaned up. Fortunately, the bore is great, and the internals seem to have escaped the moisture without a scratch. I tried to take decent pictures, but Armslist lowers the quality. If you would like more pictures, just let me know! If you are looking for a shooter version of an american classic, and don't want to damage that shiny, $1200 version you have been looking at, check this little rifle out.
